<dl id="n54144e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54144e">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54144e"> 144(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> bushy soul <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54144e"><li>FW 165.18 </li><li><a href="../../flex/fd/lexfd.htm#n54144e">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/fd/l39fd.htm#n54144e">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54144e">MS BL 47476b-469</ms> </li><li>JJA 50:275 <a name="fad9dash" href="../../ff/fdra/fda.htm#fdd8dash">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/fd/fdd8.htm#n54144e">Draft: I.6&sect;4.8</a>'</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Les repr&eacute;sentations des primitifs, comme on sait, ne se disposent pas dans les cadres de concepts hi&eacute;rarchis&eacute;s, &agrave; ar&ecirc;tes nettement tranch&eacute;es. Il est dangereux de leur demander trop de pr&eacute;cision. Je serais tent&eacute; de rapprocher ce pot-&acirc;me ext&eacute;rieure des repr&eacute;sentations tr&egrave;s r&eacute;pandues en Afrique occidentale et &eacute;quatoriale, o&ugrave; se trouvent impliqu&eacute;es des dualit&eacute;s-unit&eacute;s : les hommes-l&eacute;opards, les hommes-crocodiles, l&apos; <mark>&laquo;&acirc;me de la brousse&raquo; (bushsoul)</mark> de miss Kingsley, etc. <br><font color="green">[The representations of the primitives, as we know, are not arranged in the framework of hierarchical concepts, with clearly marked edges. It is dangerous to ask them for too much precision. I would be tempted to bring this outer pot-soul closer to representations very widespread in West and Equatorial Africa, where there are involved dualities-units: leopard-men, crocodile-men, the "soul of the bush" (bushsoul) Miss Kingsley, etc.]</font> <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 219</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
